text: I really, really hate some of the shit Jobs was known for and did. The guy was a fucking poser and at times a hardcore cunt but I appreciate his genius and massive dogged determination to push our collective creative aspirations to the limit and beyond. And GODDAMN that trailer is pure fucking myth making about this guy and I loved every fucking minute of it cause it felt so damn real. That was Jobs in those scenes, not Fassbender. That's the first time I didn't even notice Fassbender and that's the beauty of that guy's craft on display. He doesn't look a thing like Jobs yet he becomes Jobs with his attitude, demeanor and the emotion he displays when he talks and moves. Great stuff. The synth music is perfect, dare I say adding a touch of cyberpunk egomania to the entire offering. Fucking love it!

text: The opening line to this trailer where the computer could be easy to use and to look at and that everyone had one and the follow up to how it could change the status quo, it was so good and true. The personal home computer really did change the status quo. Yes IBM also had a home computer, but it wasn't easy to use, it was clunky¬†and really expensive. The¬†apple and the mac changed society forever. It is now very common to have a computer at home whether it be Microsoft or Apple, it doesn't matter, the company Apple made the computer not just a tool but also a piece of furniture that you would want in your home. Steve Jobs was indeed not an engineer, he didn't write code, what did was market the computer, he also thought of ways the computer could look better and easier to use. He brought concepts in that we may not have thought of beforehand. Sure Bill Gates brought in designs and engineering but Apple was on the scene before Microsoft. So this is why we are having another movie on Steve Jobs because he was the face of Apple, an icon.
